    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-05-08T15:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-05-08T15:00:00-05:00" n="205"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d205">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1736</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in China</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_RPS1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-05-08T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your May 4, 5 p.m.,<note n="1" xml:id="d205fn1">This telegram read: “Please reply
                        my telegram Apr. 25, 5 p.m.”</note> and April 25, 5 p.m.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d205fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_137">p. 137</ref>.</note> The
                    Department’s telegrams of May 1, 5 p.m., May 4, 4 p.m., and May 6, 5 p.m.,<note
                        n="3" xml:id="d205fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_150">pp. 150</ref> and <ref
                            target="#pg_152">152</ref>.</note> state clearly the attitude of this
                    Government towards contending factions in Russia. Strict neutrality is desirable
                    and must be observed. Although Allied governments have not recognized the Soviet
                    they are interested in stimulating its opposition to the Central powers. No
                    Allied commission for organizing representative or other government in Siberia
                    is deemed advisable.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
